--- !u!114 &1023739963
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1023739962}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 147e2430a10f38845bac3b3528774901, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialoguePanelA: {fileID: 984244409}
  dialogueTextA: {fileID: 1318580257}
  dialoguePanelB: {fileID: 1105327623}
  dialogueTextB: {fileID: 1707173822}
  lines:
  - This midnight silence... it feels heavier than a century-old graveyard.
  - Tell me, Witch. Does that crystal glass of yours hold anything... that can make
    cold blood feel a heartbeat again?
  - 'B: Welcome to the Midnight Tavern. The taste of life doesn''t come cheap, My
    Lord.'
  - I traded my soul to the abyss for a vow of protection. In return, I got this
    never-ending curse.
  - I stand on the ruins of time, watching glory fade and friends turn to dust. I
    held the crumbling walls, but I couldn't hold onto my memories.
  - "So, give me that spirit fermented under the blood-red moon. Make it thick and
    bitter like memory itself\u2014something to stir the restless blood in my veins."
  - Crush some thorny vines into it. I want a bitterness as heavy as rust. Let it
    burn through this cold shell and remind me I still have a heart.
  - "I remember thrones covered in gold\u2014the glory of decay. Add some glittering
    powder to the mix. I want to see those golden scraps flicker one last time in
    the dark."
  - And serve it in your heaviest, oldest mug. A flimsy glass can't hold centuries
    of solitude.
  charsPerSecond: 45
